    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "The string representation in dotted decimal notation. Leading zeroes are never included in the representation. As IPv4 does not define a shorthand notation for addresses with octets set to zero, these two attributes are always the same as str(addr) for IPv4 addresses. Exposing these attributes makes it easier to write display code that can handle both IPv4 and IPv6 addresses."
